Teen Facials ✨✨

Must be between the ages of 13 and 17. 18 if still in high school.  Must have a current/ valid high school ID to take advantage of teen rate.
I don’t think we talk about skincare and how it relates to mental health. How many teens struggle with self confidence because of skin issues. Hiding their beautiful/handsome faces behind hair and hoodies. So many teens suffer in silence because they think it is something that they have to deal with. Well…they don’t. Changing the things they eat and maintaining a consistent skincare routine makes such a difference . 

Parents stop wasting money trying this product and that product. Everything isn’t for everybody. Every skin type is unique . 
The First step is identifying your teen’s skin type so you can learn how to treat that skin type. That is why all teen facials start with a skin analysis.

People always asks me what order they should put their skincare products on . Well here you go💕

If you’re not double cleansing …start now!

Step 1: 1st cleanse . Cleansing balm or oil based cleanser. Removes Everything! I use @versed cleansing balm

Step 2: 2nd cleanse with water based cleanser to remove the rest. My Favorite cleanser between facials is @lovephilosophy one step facial cleaners.
After this do the white cloth test. Cloth should remain white after you blot face😎

Step 3: Toner! So important to restore the oh balance of your skin. I use @theordinary glycolic acid toner 

Step 4: Serums!! I use @dermalogica vitamin C( really helps with brightening and hyperpigmentation) and @glowrecipe hyaluronic acid serum. 

Step 5: Eye Cream! I use  @sweetchefskincare turmeric plus vitamin C, eye cream.

Step 6: Moisturizer I use @kiehls ultra facial cream.

Step 7: Sunscreen…yes SUNSCREEN! I use @blackgirlsunscreen ! Leaves NO white film on my face!! 

QUESTIONS??
 
#skincare #orderofskincare #esthetician #blackgirlsunscreen #skin #southjerseyesthetician #esty #estybestie

I really woke up out my sleep this morning like damn…ALL MY FOUNDATION, ALL MY CONCEALERS , ALL MY LIP PENCILS , ALL MY LIPSTICKS …my makeup GONE. STOLEN... It’s like it didn’t even fully click until that moment . 

I have worked so hard over the years to build my perfect kit. I have invested in all the best for my clients .I have worked for every single piece of makeup that I own. I LOVE what I do. I love how I make people feel. I have built so many great relationships with this gift God has given me. For someone to just take what you have worked hard for is heartbreaking. If I wasn’t strong this would probably take me out the game but it won’t . God gave me this gift for a purpose and that purpose I will continue to fulfill. I will bounce back even better . Clients just be patient with me 
Love y’all 🤍

Yes…my makeup kit was stolen but my talent…my gift … WAS NOT. Do you know whose child I AM?????

This client came in and my mind was racing brain all over the place because I knew I didn’t have my kit . But I refused to cancel any other clients . I NEVER CANCEL ON CLIENTS . This client would’ve never known that I was in shambles on the inside I only showed her my greatness on the outside . 

I only had foundation that was too dark for her and I took that , some white eye paint , some yellow and a little blue and made 3 shades …one for her base , one for her highlight and one for her contour and I painted . And at that moment I knew this was only a minor set back and this comeback is about to be Remarkable!
